Conjugates
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Two group elements are called conjugate, written 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{1}\sim g_{2}$
\end_inset

 if there exists a element 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 such that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
g_{1}=gg_{2}g^{-1}
\]

\end_inset

Conjugacy is an equivalence relation, i.e.
 
\end_layout

